Would you rather be rich and alone or be poor and find true love?

I would rather be poor and find true love. Being poor is a situation I can overcome. I might not ever become rich, but I would have the things that really count in life: True love, caring, dedication, devotion, companionship. My husband and I would be able to find ways to survive financially. It might not be easy but it would be worth it. 

Being rich and alone would  be harder. You would begin to hate people because you would realize that people don't truly care for you, only what you can give them or do for them. 

There is a chance that being poor and having your true love wouldn't work out either. A lot of couples, who truly love each other, fight and break up over money issues. Lack of money to take care of one's loved ones can change a person's personality. How many horror stories have been on the news about a spouse that committed domestic violence, or even murder and it is said about that person that they used to be a wonderful person until losing their job or financial troubles began and they started drinking or doing drugs. 

Human beings need love and companionship. Now that is not to say I wouldn't prefer being Rich and having my True love together. We would be able to accomplish so much more in life and help others.

I would rather be poor and find true love because companionship is more important to me than any monetary value.

Her husband was trying to save her and himself but he was weighed down by his own clothing and boots. I quickly untied our boat and my dad rowed as fast as he could. Luckily I was able to hang over the boat and reach as far as I could down into the water and reach the womans hair. We rowed them to shore and they were both saved. This was very hard for a 10 year old.
Have you ever saved an animals life? How about a persons life?

I haven't ever saved an animals life, nor a humans life. However, in the moment, I thought I did save a humans life. I was leaving work at night and traveling on the West Seattle bridge. It was empty. I was driving westbound and a car on the other side was traveling eastbound. All of a sudden it started doing barrel rolls and landed right side up right next to the little cement barriers that divide the highway you know? I had came to a screeching halt, ran out and took their pulse. Called 911. Waited with them. A taxi of guys coming back from the bar also pulled over and started praying around the person. It was crazy. They barely had a pulse and weren't using a seatbelt, because they were upside down in the drivers seat. I got a call from the offer closing the investigation like a year later telling me they passed away. It was really sad. I'll never forget that moment. I wish I could've done more.

14 Simple Gardening Tips and Tricks
From using leftover coffee beans to preventing dirt from getting underneath fingernails, master gardener Paul James shares his top 14 tips and shortcuts to make spring gardening a breeze.
Pinterest
Facebook
Twitter
Email
Assorted Flowerpots
Little clay pots make great cloches for protecting young plants from overnight frosts.
Here, the latest tips and tricks from Paul James, host of Gardening by the Yard:

1. To remove the salt deposits that form on clay pots, combine equal parts white vinegar, rubbing alcohol and water in a spray bottle. Apply the mixture to the pot and scrub with a plastic brush. Let the pot dry before you plant anything in it.

2. To prevent accumulating dirt under your fingernails while you work in the garden, draw your fingernails across a bar of soap and you'll effectively seal the undersides of your nails so dirt can't collect beneath them. Then, after you've finished in the garden, use a nailbrush to remove the soap and your nails will be sparkling clean.

3. To prevent the line on your string trimmer from jamming or breaking, treat with a spray vegetable oil before installing it in the trimmer.

4. Turn a long-handled tool into a measuring stick! Lay a long-handled garden tool on the ground, and next to it place a tape measure. Using a permanent marker, write inch and foot marks on the handle. When you need to space plants a certain distance apart (from just an inch to several feet) you'll already have a measuring device in your hand.

What is pseudoscience? Give some examples.

Pseudoscience includes beliefs, theories, or practices that have been or are considered scientific, but have no basis in scientific fact. This could mean they were disproved scientifically, cant be tested or lack evidence to support them. 


Conversion Therapy - Attempts to change a persons sexual preference from homosexual to heterosexual
Hypnosis - A method of deep relaxation where the subject is open to suggestions
Primal Therapy - Belief that experiences before and during birth influence the way our life unfolds
Polygraphy - A lie detector test used to determine if the subject is lying by measuring changes in some vital signs
What is pseudoscience? Give some examples.

Pseudoscience is a collection of beliefs or practices mistakenly regarded as being based on scientific method. Some examples of pseudoscience include: 2012 Phenomenon - Expectations that 2012 would bring large-scale disasters or even the end of the world
Ancient Astronauts - Proposes that aliens have visited the earth in the past and influenced our civilization
Astrology - Belief that humans are affected by the position of celestial bodies
Crop Circles - Some believe these are made by aliens
Face on Mars - A rock formation on Mars that resembles a face and is believed to be evidence of life
Flat Earth Society - Claims the Earth is flat and disc-shaped
Moon Landing Conspiracy - Contends the original moon landing was faked.

There was a young asian man working at a tall corporate office. He worked in the mail room and would go from the first floor to the CEO's office at the top of the building delivering mail all day everyday. The CEO noticed how diligent and attentive he was and remarked one day about how hard of a worker he was. "I would like to offer you a promotion. You never take sick days and you always make it to my office with my mail on time. We have an opening in the room where we keep the supplies. The position would require you to come in first thing in the morning, 7 am, before anyone else is here. Would you like to take it?" The asian man replied, "Oh yes! I can do supplies!" The CEO was pleased and told the man to be there at 7 am sharp. The next day the CEO arrived at 7 and decided to check on the newly promoted employee. He walked down to the supply room to find that all the lights were off! "He couldn't even make it in on time? First day at the new position and he no-shows..." So he turns around and flips on the lights; out from behind the copy machine the asian man springs up and shouts, "SUPPLIES!!!"

How do you make soap?

Some of the recipes for making soap say coconut oil, olive oil, some other kind of oil like grapeseed or sunflower, lye and cooled purified or distilled water. You will want to cover your work area and wear protective wear. Measure your water in a quart canning jar, have a spoon ready and measure your Lye. Pour the lye into the water while stirring. Stand back to avoid the fumes and when the water is clear you can start on the next step. In a pint jar you can the 3 oils, heat that in the microwave for a minute and then place the oils in a pan to heat. Check the temp of the oils and make sure they are about 120 degrees and wait for both to cool to about 95 to 105 degrees, this is very critical for making the best soaps. When both are at the right temp pour the oils into a mixing bowl and then slowly add the lye stirring till all is mixed together. Stir by hand for 5 minutes. After 5 minutes you can keep stirring or use immersion blender, the soap mixture will lighten in color and become thick. When it looks like vanilla pudding you are good to go.

How do you tie-dye clothes?

To tie-dye clothes, first you need to wrap rubber bands around the thing you want to tie-dye. You can follow a pattern, or just tie it wherever you want. You can also roll it into a spiral and then wrap your rubber bands around that. Then, when you're done tying, you can either dip it in the dye, or use a squirt bottle to apply it. Follow the instructions that came with the dye. You should let it sit for at least a few hours so they dye has time to set. Then you rinse it out with cold water, take off the rubber bands, and wash it one more time in the washing machine.

How do you soft boil an egg?

A soft boiled egg should have firm whites and a runny yolk. Cover the eggs in a saucepan with cold water. It all comes down to timing.  
Bring the water to a boil and then lower to a simmer.  Begin timing the eggs.  Five minutes for 1 or 2 eggs for a runny yolk.  Cook seven
minutes for a firm but runny yolk.  More than 2 eggs add a few seconds to the time. More than 4 eggs use another saucepan or cook in batches.

Tell me a feel-good story you heard recently.

My dog Otis knows how to count.  He loves to pick up pine cones in his mouth.  We went for a walk the other day, and I kicked a pine cone.  He ran and picked it up.  I said "Otis you have one pine cone."  We walked a little further and I kicked another one.  Natural, being a labrador, he ran and got it. "Otis, you have two pine cones. "  He had both in his mouth.  A few minutes later he came back with a third in his mouth.  "Otis?  Do you have three?"  Our walk ended.  We played this game a few times. One day I went out and said, "Otis get me one pine cone." Sure enough he came back with one.  Then I told him to get two.  Sure enough he came back with two pine cones in his mouth.  He also passed the test for three pine cones.  But I could never get him to get four.  It seemed like his brain could only count to three.  Any more than that he would just bring back however many would fit in his mouth.  We called that number "fourses and fives", which meant anything over three.
